Privacy Policy

Last Updated: October 28, 2025
App Name: A2z Soundbox
Company: Coretility

1. Overview

This Privacy Policy explains how A2z Soundbox (“we”, “our”, or “us”) handles your information when you use the App.
We value your privacy and ensure that your personal data is protected.

2. Information We Collect
a) Notification Access (Local Processing)

The App reads payment-related notifications (e.g., UPI transaction alerts) to generate sound alerts.

All processing is done locally on your device.

No notification content, sender information, or banking data is transmitted to our servers.

b) Analytics and Diagnostics

We may collect anonymous analytics data such as:

App version and device model

Crash logs

General usage statistics

This helps us improve performance, reliability, and feature quality.

3. Data Sharing

We do not share your personal or notification data with any third parties.
Anonymous analytics may be shared with trusted service providers (like Google Analytics or Firebase) for performance insights.

4. Data Security

We implement reasonable technical and organizational safeguards to protect your data from unauthorized access or misuse.
Because most data stays on-device, the risk of exposure is minimal.

5. Your Rights

You can revoke notification access at any time through your device’s Settings → Notifications → Notification Access.
You can also uninstall the App to stop all processing immediately.

6. Children’s Privacy

The App is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children.

7. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically.
The latest version will always be available on our website or app store listing. Your continued use of the App signifies acceptance of any updates.
